% rebase('layout.tpl', title='Biography of C418')

<style>
    body
    {
        background: linear-gradient(to bottom, #4a90e2, #6a5acd, #483d8b);
        color: white;
        text-align: center;
    }
    .container
    {
        max-width: 800px;
        margin: auto;
        padding: 20px;
    }
    img
    {
        border-radius: 15px;
        box-shadow: 0px 4px 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
    }
    .info
    {
        background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
        padding: 15px;
        border-radius: 10px;
        margin-top: 15px;
    }
    .links 
    {
        margin-top: 20px;
    }
    .links a 
    {
        color: #ffcc00;
        text-decoration: none;
        font-weight: bold;
        margin: 0 10px;
    }
    .links a:hover 
    {
        text-decoration: underline;
    }
</style>

<div class="container">
    <h1>Biography of C418</h1>
    <img src="/static/images/c418.jpg" alt="C418" width="300">
    <p>
        Daniel Rosenfeld, better known as C418, is a German composer and sound engineer, best known for his Minecraft soundtracks.
        His music combines elements of ambient and chiptune, creating a unique and immersive atmosphere.
    </p>
    
    <div class="info">
        <h2>Quick Facts about C418</h2>
        <ul style="list-style-type: none; padding: 0;">
            <li><strong>Real name:</strong> Daniel Rosenfeld</li>
            <li><strong>Date of birth:</strong> May 9, 1989</li>
            <li><strong>Country:</strong> Germany</li>
            <li><strong>Famous albums:</strong> <i>Minecraft Volume Alpha</i>, <i>Minecraft Volume Beta</i></li>
        </ul>
    </div>
    
    <div class="info">
        <h2>Career and Style</h2>
        <p>
            C418 started producing music in the early 2000s, experimenting with electronic and ambient sounds.
            His breakthrough came with the soundtrack for Minecraft, which captivated millions of players worldwide.
            Apart from Minecraft, he has released several independent albums, exploring different electronic music styles.
        </p>
    </div>
    
    <div class="links">
        <h2>Explore More</h2>
        <a href="/songs">Songs</a>
        <a href="/sheet-music">Sheet Music</a>
    </div>
</div>